Package com.esri.mo2.ui.ren

Provides support for various symbology renderers used in MapObjects--Java Edition.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
IRenderer Provides the common methods for all renderer related user interface classes.
 

Class Summary
ClassBreaks Provides a definition for rendering ClassBreaks, which includes color, label, and break range (minimum and maximum values).
ClassBreaksRendererUI Provides an user interface to the class breaks renderer's parameters.
ColorEditor Implements a dialog for editing a color.
ColorRenderer Provides a color renderer for use in color chooser classes.
ExtensionFileFilter A convenience implementation of FileFilter that filters out all files except for type extensions it knows about.
LabelEffects Implements an user interface to set label effects attributes.
LabelLinePlacement Implements an user interface for the parameters of label line placement.
LabelPointPlacement Provides an user interface for parameters of point placement.
LabelRendererUI Implements an user interface for label renderer parameters.
LayerGeneral Implements an user interface or a panel for general parameters of a layer.
LayerProperties Implements an user interface which allows users to change the properties of a layer such as its renderer and symbology.
PlacementButton Represent a point label's placement location as a set of radio buttons.
RendererTableModel Provides a common table model for displaying renderer related data such as class breaks.
RendererUIContainer Implements an user interface for an user to select renderers for individual layers.
ScaleDependentRenderer Provides an user interface for manipulating scale dependent renderer's parameters.
ShieldDialog This class provides a dialog for an user to select or change parameters associated with a shield.
SimpleRenderer Provides an user interface for handling a simple renderer's parameters.
UniqueValues Provides a data structure for unique values.
UniqueValuesRendererUI Implements an user interface for handling unique values renderer's parameters.
Util Provides common utility functions for the Renderer's UI package.
 

Package com.esri.mo2.ui.ren Description

Provides support for various symbology renderers used in MapObjects--Java Edition.
